		<td>
		<b> Research Statement </b><br><br>
		<img src="img/3d_CoverImage.png" style="width:100px;height:100px;padding-right:20px;" align="left">
		My name is Shreyas Skandan and currently work as an Application Developer at the University of Pennsylvania. I work at G.R.A.S.P at the <b>Vijay Kumar Lab</b> under <a href="https://www.cis.upenn.edu/~cjtaylor/home.html">Prof. Camillo Jose Taylor</a> and I previously worked at the <b>Rehabilitation Robotics Lab</b>. My research is in <i>Deep Learning</i> and <i>Machine Perception</i>. I'm currently exploring the applications of deep learning with visual data as well as applying stereoscopy to effeciently solve tracking problems. <br><br>
		I recently graduated from the M.S.E in Robotics programme at Penn where I worked on my Master's Thesis under <a href="https://www.cis.upenn.edu/~cjtaylor/home.html">Prof. Camillo Jose Taylor</a>, which was <i>"A survey of High Performance Dense Stereo Algorithms for Real Time Depth Estimation" -- a video of the presentation can be found <a href="https://youtu.be/QvHdOKvwGQw?t=1h11m34s">HERE</a></i><br>
		<br>
		</td>
